name: molybdopterin molybdotransferase
classes: Molybdenumtransferases or tungstentransferases with sulfide groups as acceptors
reaction: adenylyl-molybdopterin + molybdate = molybdenum cofactor + AMP + H2O [RN:R09735]
comment: Catalyses the insertion of molybdenum into the ene-dithiol group of molybdopterin. In eukaryotes this reaction is catalysed by the N-terminal domain of a fusion protein whose C-terminal domain catalyses EC 2.7.7.75, molybdopterin adenylyltransferase. Requires divalent cations such as Mg2+ or Zn2+ for activity.
